modules.description: Provides functions to perform HTTP GET and POST requests, handle headers, and parse JSON responses. Works with strings, associative lists, and OCaml's built-in JSON types. Used to fetch remote data, submit form submissions, and integrate with REST APIs in web applications.

Provides access to detailed HTTP response information including total request time, redirect count, status code, headers, and body. Contains functions to extract and manipulate response data from HTTP transactions. Examples include retrieving the total duration of a request, checking the number of redirects followed, and inspecting response headers or body content. Supports programmatic handling of HTTP interactions within an Lwt-based asynchronous framework.
